Meanwhile, Israel's hardliners will draw the opposite conclusions.
In military terms, Hamas has been put in a box.
The Iron Dome missile interception system has proven effective and many Hamas missiles have been destroyed.
The Israelis will be able to sleep on their heels for a while.
In terms of diplomacy, America renews its unwavering support, and many European countries have blamed Hamas for the latest wave of violence.
