Although rocket attacks from Gaza have killed about 30 Israelis since 2004, Israel has been spared suicide bombings, thanks in part to the separation barrier that encircles the West Bank, the main piece of what could be a Palestinian state, and protects Jewish settlements that continue to expand despite their illegality under international law.
Mr Netanyahu, whose Likud party has merged with an even more hawkish party, that of leader Avigdor Lieberman in the run-up to the January 22 election, has the upper hand.
Why coddle these damn Palestinians by giving them a state?
