At the moment, this judgment is not respected.
It's a problem between a South American country and a Central American country.
Conflicts are inevitable, but they must be overcome by the will to move forward together.
We must tackle them as a whole to overcome them and move forward.
At the same time, he expressed confidence in the good resolution of the maritime border dispute between Peru and Chile in the same court and said that it would be "beneficial for Latin America to go to the international courts if both countries agree to accept such a firm judgment".
Referring to the possibility of his running for a third consecutive term in the upcoming presidential elections in Ecuador, he said he looked at the possibility "with great optimism and joy, although it is sometimes quite difficult".
