Hector "Hetin" Reyes "Basketball is my whole life"
The basketball globe-trotter "Hetin" Reyes spent more than 60 years of his life in relation with the field and, thanks to it, traveled all over the world.
Few people in Puerto Rico have as much knowledge of the history of local basketball as Hector "Hetin" Reyes.
The reason is that before a brain hemorrhage put him in a wheelchair in 2008, Reyes was immersed in the sport for more than 60 years, whether as a minor league player, a member of the national basketball team, a manager and national team leader, the BSN, with the Vaqueros de Bayamón, or as president of the basketball federation.
"I have worn several caps in basketball throughout my life, and even several at the same time, like when I was president of the BSN, general manager of the national team and president of the federation during the 90s", Reyes recalls during a visit from Primera Hora to his home in Bayamón, where he resides with Isabel, his faithful wife of over 50 years.
"Basketball is my whole life".
Reyes is not exaggerating when he makes that statement.
The walls of his home, almost all of which are decorated with photos and memorabilia of his extraordinary journey, bear witness to this.
